com.raweng.built

Class BuiltInstallation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltInstallation

  • public class BuiltInstallation
extends java.lang.Object
    BuiltInstallation class for creating installation and subscribe/unsubscribe for push notifications against a channel.
    Author:
    raw engineering, Inc

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      BuiltInstallation()
      Creates new BuiltInstallation instance to update/delete installations or subscribe/unsubscribe to installation channels.

      • createInstallation

        public void createInstallation(java.lang.String deviceToken,
                      java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> installationChannels,
                      com.raweng.built.BuiltResultCallBack callback)
        Create a new installation. Request to create installation data.
        Parameters:
        deviceToken - Registration token which user received from google server for GCM.
        installationChannels - channels subscribe to. Channels can have the values below: 
        
//To notify when new class is created inside an application.
 class.create  

//To notify when new object is created inside class with <class_uid>.
 <class_uid>.object.create  

//To notify when class with given <class_uid> is updated in an application.
 <class_uid>.update  

//To notify when object with given <object_uid> is updated inside class with <class_uid> in an application.
 <class_uid>.<object_uid>.update  

//To notify when class with given <class_uid> is deleted in an application.
 <class_uid>.delete  

//To notify when object with given <object_uid> is deleted inside class with <class_uid> in an application.
 <class_uid>.<object_uid>.delete  

//To notify when any class in an application is updated.
 class.update  

//To notify when any class in an application is deleted.
 class.delete  

//To notify when any object of class with <class_uid> in an application is updated.
 <class_uid>.object.update  

//To notify when any object of class with <class_uid> in an application is deleted.
 <class_uid>.object.delete  

//To notify when any upload is created.
 upload.create  

//To notify when an upload with <upload_uid> is updated.
 <upload_uid>.update  

//To notify when an upload with <upload_uid> is deleted.
 <upload_uid>.delete  

//To notify when any upload is updated.
 upload.update  

//To notify when any upload is deleted.
 upload.delete  

 You can add custom channels as well.
        callback - BuiltResultCallBack object to notify the application when the request has completed.

      • subscribeToChannels

        public void subscribeToChannels(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> installationChannels,
                       com.raweng.built.BuiltResultCallBack callback)
        Subscribe an installation to more channels.
        Using this resource you can add more channels to your subscription list.
        Parameters:
        installationChannels - Array of channel we wish to subscribe to. channels subscribe to. Channels can have the values below: 
         
//To notify when new class is created inside an application.
 class.create  

//To notify when new object is created inside class with <class_uid>.
 <class_uid>.object.create  

//To notify when class with given <class_uid> is updated in an application.
 <class_uid>.update  

//To notify when object with given <object_uid> is updated inside class with <class_uid> in an application.
 <class_uid>.<object_uid>.update  

//To notify when class with given <class_uid> is deleted in an application.
 <class_uid>.delete  

//To notify when object with given <object_uid> is deleted inside class with <class_uid> in an application.
 <class_uid>.<object_uid>.delete  

//To notify when any class in an application is updated.
 class.update  

//To notify when any class in an application is deleted.
 class.delete  

//To notify when any object of class with <class_uid> in an application is updated.
 <class_uid>.object.update  

//To notify when any object of class with <class_uid> in an application is deleted.
 <class_uid>.object.delete  

//To notify when any upload is created.
 upload.create  

//To notify when an upload with <upload_uid> is updated.
 <upload_uid>.update  

//To notify when an upload with <upload_uid> is deleted.
 <upload_uid>.delete  

//To notify when any upload is updated.
 upload.update  

//To notify when any upload is deleted.
 upload.delete  


 You can add custom channels as well.
